    <abstract>
      <t>This document defines a portion of the Management Information Base
   (MIB) for use with network management protocols in the Internet
   community.  In particular, it describes managed objects used to
   manage key management implementations including asymmetric keys,
   symmetric keys, trust anchors, and cryptographic-related firmware.</t>
